description:
In this episode, we learn of the reigns of Manasseh and Josiah. One led the nation in idol worship, and the other broke the pattern in his family, served God, and led the nation to worship God. We don't have to repeat the same mistakes as our forefathers. Instead, we can each have an experience with God that makes a difference.
